[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/ogust"]
[Student "S"]
{Having opened 2\S, you reply to partner's Ogust 2NT bid with 3\H, showing a maximum hand but with a poor suit. Partner says 4\S and you pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "W:KJ8.KQT9.2.JT963 T62.84.AQ9873.74 Q754.J632.JT.KQ5 A93.A75.K654.A82"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
pass 2D pass 2NT pass 3D pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "a0522312d4d038e8c1444cba96cd416dee0b6dc19601b2a2c38832b02ff957bc"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/ogust"]
[Student "S"]
{You could just guess between pass, 3NT, or 5\D.

But you use Ogust instead. Partner responds 3\D.  

Partner's 3\D bid shows a minimum hand but a good suit, which should mean two of the top three honors. Your \DK tells you that partner has a 6-card \D  suit headed by the A Q. With three outside Aces you can count 9 tricks - you bid 3NT.}

